- Component is a Kubernetes Deployment (not CronJob), triggered by an
  internal Spring @Scheduled cron, reading the cron expression from
  env var ${scheduler_cron}.
- Chunk size = 1, single Spring Batch step, commit-per-item, sequential
  processing of seven Visa RTSI queues in one job execution.
- Seven queues: FIRSTCHARGEBACK (AWAITING_ACTION_BQ_DISPUTE), PREARB
  (AWAITING_ACTION_BQ_PRE_FILING), ARB (INCOMING_BQ_ARBITRATIONS),
  ACCEPT (INCOMING_BQ_ACCEPTANCES_RECEIVED), RECALL (INCOMING_BQ_RECALLS),
  PRECOMP (INCOMING_BQ_PRECOMPLIANCES), COMP (INCOMING_BQ_COMPLIANCES).
- Queue order runtime-controlled by ${queue_name_list}. Exhaustion signal
  is Visa status code I-300600000.
- Pagination is page-number offset-based; all pages for a queue loaded
  into memory before processing begins.
- 9-step pipeline as: Platform mapping → IDP token fetch → Rules check →
  HyperSearch → PIN validation (networkId=0002 only) → migrationStatus=Y
  hardcoded → Case lookup (PRECOMP / COMP / generic variants) → PAN
  encryption → Writer + MarkAsRead.
- Null-return silent skip pattern at every enrichment failure. No DLQ.
- Three feature flags from K8s Secret gcp-visa-disputes-processor-batch-
  secrets: coreDataNeedToMigrate, removeItemFromQueueDisabled,
  readSpecificItemFromQueue. Effects as previously documented.
- MarkAsRead gate: PIN proceeds; CORE only if coreDataNeedToMigrate=true;
  all suppressed if removeItemFromQueueDisabled=true. RECALL items map to
  CORE platform (networkId=0002) — MarkAsRead behaviour depends entirely
  on coreDataNeedToMigrate.
- Writes only to wdp.chbk_outbox_row. Constants: event_type=
  CHARGEBACK_PROCESS, c_case_ntwk=VISA, created_by=WVDPB, retry_count=0.
  Payload is full CommonEvent JSON with HPAN (not clear PAN) in
  accountNumber.
- Duplicate check is application-level SELECT-before-INSERT on
  (networkCaseId + networkPhaseId + disputeStage); RECALL items are
  exempted from this check.
- PAN is encrypted via wdp-encryption-service at step 8 before the outbox
  write. No clear PAN is written anywhere persistent.
- No @EnableKafka, no KafkaTemplate, no Kafka producer config class in
  main source. spring-kafka / kafka-clients / aws-msk-iam-auth declared
  in POM but not wired.
- No Resilience4j dependency. No connection or read timeout on
  RestTemplate (SimpleClientHttpRequestFactory default).
- @Retryable with 3 attempts × 2s delay on: GetBatchQueue, HyperSearch,
  VisaTransSearch, MarkAsRead, Rules Service, Encryption Service.
  @Retryable is ABSENT on: IDP token GET, Case Search GET.
- Resource profile: memory req 256Mi / limit 2048Mi; CPU not set
  (burstable QoS); OTel Java agent injected; Spring Actuator present;
  Logstash appender present; RollingUpdate maxSurge=1 maxUnavailable=0;
  no HPA, no PDB, no topology spread.

